=====================================================
Calculate player performances from chess game results
=====================================================

.. contents::


Description
===========

This package provides methods to calculate player performances and performance statistics.

Calculate player performances from a set of game results.

Display a list of player performances based only on the given results.

Display various calculations and statistics for the given results.


Installation Instructions
=========================

Usually this package will be installed by installing `ChessResults`_.

Install the package by typing

   python setup.py install

at the command prompt with setup.py in the current directory.

You may need to give the path and version of Python depending on your system's configuration:

   <path to python>/python<version> setup.py install

   For example

      C:\\Python33\\python setup.py install

         on Microsoft Windows or

      python3.3 setup.py install

         on Unix-like systems.

Use `Python`_ 3.3 or later.


Run
===

The command to run this package is:

   python -m chesscalc.calculate

You may need to give the path and version of Python depending on your system's configuration:

   <path to python>/python<version> -m chesscalc.calculate

   For example

      C:\\Python33\\python -m chesscalc.calculate

         on Microsoft Windows or

      python3.3 -m chesscalc.calculate

         on Unix-like systems.

Or use the facilities of your desktop (Microsoft Windows, GNOME, KDE, ...) to set up a convenient way of starting chessgames.


Notes
=====

The current implementation does just enough to support the `ChessResults`_ package.


.. _`Python`: https://python.org
.. _`ChessResults`: http://solentware.co.uk/grading.html
